We apply the Gauss-Jordan reduction algorithm to invert 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{array}{rl}
\begin{array}{c}
\\R_{2}-R_{1}\\
R_{3}-R_{1}
\end{array} & \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 1 & 1\\
1 & 2 & 3\\
1 & 3 & 6
\end{array}\right|\left.\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 0 & 0\\
0 & 1 & 0\\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{array}\right]\\
\\\begin{array}{c}
\\\\R_{3}-2R_{1}
\end{array} & \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 1 & 1\\
0 & 1 & 2\\
0 & 2 & 5
\end{array}\right|\left.\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 0 & 0\\
-1 & 1 & 0\\
-1 & 0 & 1
\end{array}\right]\\
\\\begin{array}{c}
R_{1}-R_{2}\\
\\\\\end{array} & \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 1 & 1\\
0 & 1 & 2\\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{array}\right|\left.\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 0 & 0\\
-1 & 1 & 0\\
1 & -2 & 1
\end{array}\right]\\
\\\begin{array}{c}
R_{1}+R_{3}\\
R_{2}-2R_{3}\\
\\\end{array} & \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 0 & -1\\
0 & 1 & 2\\
